POLICE minister Bheki Cele has released the quarterly crime statistics, and the first three months of 2022 were violent and brutal. According to statistics, the fourth quarter of the 2021/22 fiscal year saw an increase in murders, sexual violence and assaults compared to the same time period the previous one. They indicated that the country recorded a 22,2% murder increase between 1 January and March 31 while reported murders increased from 4 976 to 6 083 – a rise of 1 107. The minister further said sexual offences rose by 1 676, from 12 123 cases to 13 799, resulting in an increase of 13,7%. This while attempted murders recorded an increase of 1 135, rising from 4 582 to 5 717 – 24,8% increase while with a 6 575 rise, assault GBH went from 36 417 to 42 992. “A total of 2 268 people were murdered in public places such as an open field, street, parking area and abandoned building. The second most likely place for murder to occur is at the home of the victim or the perpetrator as a total of 1 350 people were killed in that environment,” said Cele. Liquor outlets and public transport such as buses, taxis or trains were the third and fourth most likely places for people to be killed in South Africa. A breakdown of sexual offence crimes indicated that rape saw reported cases rise by 1 300. The category saw a 7% increase, from 9 582 to 10 818 cases, while attempted sexual offences in this period increased by 114, from 423 incidents to 547, an increase of 26,3%. The fourth quarter also saw carjackings increase by 889, from 4513 to 5 402, while robberies at residential and non-residential residences decreased by 0,4% and 3,5% respectively.